article.headline: St. Francis, NY 62, Hartford 59
article.story: EDS: St. Francis, N.Y. 62, Hartford 59. NEW YORK (AP) -- Robert Hines scored 21 points to lead St. Francis, N.Y. to a 62-59 victory over Hartford on Friday night. The Terriers (1-0) lost their first 12 games last season under then-first-year coach Brian Nash and finished 9-22. Ricky Cadell's third 3-pointer of the game gave St. Francis the lead for good at 60-57. Joe Zeglinski led the Hawks (0-1) with 13 points, while Warren McLendon and Mike Turner both added 10. Turner had 10 rebounds. Hartford opened the game with a 19-2 run and were up 30-19 on a jumper by Jaret Von Rosenberg 1:40 into the second half. Zeglinksi's 3-pointer with 8:35 to go gave Hartford a 46-42 lead, but the Terriers went on a 7-0 run that was capped by a 3 by Kayden Ayeni.
